mattglbrt.com
=============

Matt Gilbert's personal site — the artist hub behind The Hobbinomicon and the
rest of the brands. A text-first command-center: it links out to the channels,
shops, and project sites, hosts a free-form Log, surfaces the latest videos, and
takes commission inquiries.

Built on the Entropic textmode theme (retro fixed-width / ASCII aesthetic).
Static Astro build, deployed on Netlify.


Quick start
-----------

    pnpm install --frozen-lockfile
    pnpm dev        # local dev server
    pnpm build      # static build -> dist/  (runs checks first)
    pnpm check      # astro check + biome
    pnpm format     # biome format --write

Requires Node >= 22 and pnpm.


Layout
------

    src/config/             site, volumes, appearance, effects, and videos config
    src/content/philes/     Log posts (.phile files), grouped into volumes
    src/images/             post images (optimized at build by astro:assets)
    src/components/         Astro components
    src/pages/              routes: home, /videos, /commissions, volumes
    src/modules/            phile + volume loading, textmode engine, videos feed
    netlify/functions/      scheduled daily rebuild (keeps the video feed fresh)

Main knobs:

    src/config/site.ts         home page text + the link hub
    src/config/volumes.ts      volume titles + sorting (the Log is volume 1)
    src/config/videos.ts       YouTube channels for the /videos feed
    src/config/appearance.ts   colors, fonts, text cell sizing


Writing a Log post
-------------------

Add a `.phile` file under `src/content/philes/volume-1/log/`. A phile is YAML
frontmatter fenced by `---`, then plain fixed-width body text:

    ---
    title: "Post title"
    date: 2026-06-02
    author: "Matt Gilbert"
    ---

    Body text. Layout is preserved (ASCII frames, tables, diagrams render as
    written) and prose wraps at 80 columns.

Required frontmatter: `title`, `date`, `author`. Optional: `lang`, `order`,
`slug`, `redacted`.

In the body:

    Images   put one on its own line: ![alt text](/images/folder/file.jpg)
             The file lives under src/images/folder/file.jpg and is optimized
             (responsive webp + click-to-zoom) automatically. The alt becomes
             the caption.
    Links    bare http(s):// and www. URLs become clickable automatically.
    Color    inline ink: #[role|text]  (e.g. #[G|green]). Roles and dense ANSI
             overlays are documented in the textmode modules.


Videos
------

`/videos` pulls each channel's YouTube RSS feed at build time, merges and sorts
them, and renders the latest. Add channel IDs in `src/config/videos.ts`. A
Netlify scheduled function triggers a daily rebuild so new uploads appear
without manual posts (set the `BUILD_HOOK_URL` env var — see `netlify.toml`).


Commissions
-----------

`/commissions` is a showcase plus a Netlify Forms inquiry form. Toggle
availability with the `COMMISSION_STATUS` constant at the top of
`src/pages/commissions/index.astro`. Configure where submissions go in the
Netlify UI (Forms -> notifications).


Deploy
------

Netlify, static. `netlify.toml` sets the build command and publish dir. Pushing
to `main` triggers a deploy. Netlify Forms and the scheduled rebuild function
are picked up from the build.


